<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="diagnostic description">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Diagnostic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Mandible lacinia mobilis a stemmed, distally expanded, smooth blade</emphasis>
. Maxilla 1 inner plate with pappose setae lining inner margin; palp 2-articulate. Maxilla 2 inner and outer plates subequal in width, inner plate slightly shorter than outer. Maxilliped palp article 4 reduced or well developed. Gnathopod 1 coxa large, margins diverging distally; basis slender, linear; dactylus small, simple, highly modified with apical tip. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Pereopod 3 carpus compressed, wider than long</emphasis>
. Pereopod 4 coxa with weakly-developed, subacutely produced posteroventral lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1926" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Scopelocheiropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has some variable characters, most importantly the absence of a molar in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Vinogradov" authorityYear="2004" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublitoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(present in the both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1926" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abyssalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ledoyer" baseAuthorityYear="1986" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis armata" order="Amphipoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Scopelocheiropsis armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the blunt, reduced maxilliped palp article 4 in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1926" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abyssalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(well-developed in the other two species). Nevertheless, the distinctively compressed carpus of pereopods 3 and 4, as well as the stemmed and distally expanded lacinia mobilis are strong diagnostic characters which separate these taxa from other groups.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
